m to solve the problem. We\nalso prove an $\\Omega(r / \\mathrm{polylog}(n))$ lower bound for the space\nneeded by a streaming algorithm with $< 1/2^{\\mathrm{polylog}(n)}$ error\nagainst \"white-box\" adversaries that can see the internal state of the\nalgorithm, but not predict its future random decisions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Nov 2022 19:52:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-11"}
